decision_conditions:
&lt;p&gt;Prior to the commencement of the relevant part of the works, detailed drawings/full particulars of the proposed development showing the matters set out below must be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, in writing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
a) details and samples of all materials&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
b) full details of black metal balustrades&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
c) &amp;nbsp;1:20 elevations of the proposed windows showing the pane pattern and 1:5 sections showing the materials, integral glazing bars, frames and 12mm glazing units.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;d) details of sedum roof&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
REASON:&amp;nbsp;To ensure that the external appearance of the building is satisfactory and does not detract from the character and visual amenity of the Brownswood &amp;amp; Stoke Newington reservoirs, filter beds and New River Conservation Area.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No development shall commence, other than works of demolition, until surface water (overland flow) and groundwater
flood mitigation measures have been submitted to and agreed, in writing with the Local Planning Authority in consultation with the
LLFA. The development shall thereafter only be implemented in accordance with the approved details.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: In the interest of flood risk mitigation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
